Rating: 4
Needed modifications, but a great base recipe. I made it for 40 people and made the following additions/changes: 1.) started with dried black-eyed peas, soaked and drained. Way cheaper. 2.) Added some honey, raisins, cumin, garlic, coconut milk, peas and chopped collard greens. 3.) Served it with a side of Patak brand mango-chili chutney for optional spice. 4.) Definitely make the day before and let it sit overnight. Flavors are much better the next day.

Rating: 3
I liked this recipe, even though I modified it to meet my spicy tastes. I used vegetable broth instead of water and doubled the curry. The tomatoes I added were canned/stewed tomatoes with a little jalapeno in them. Planning to serve over rice, and maybe adding a dollop of plain yogurt with the cilantro. Yummy!

