Rating: 4
I got fresh black-eyed peas from the market and needed a recipe... really liked this one; added some cinnamon which we thought was great. Make sure not to skip the cilantro - it really pulls it all together.

Rating: 3
I rated this a solid 3 forks. I added a pinch of fennel seed powder, 1/2 tsp of cayenne and 1/2 tsp of coriander seed powder. I also doubled the amount ginger and added 2 large minced garlic cloves to the saute. This definitely combatted the blandness. Adding a little water helped with the consistency as well.

Rating: 3
This dish is fun because you can play around with it. I omitted the potato and added an extra 1/2 cup of tomato, a 10 oz package of frozen spinach, a heaping 1/2 teaspoon of cayenne, salt, and an extra teaspoon of curry powder. I also added some water because I thought it was a little dry at first. It was delicious served over brown rice.

