Rating: 4
I thought this was great! I used dried black eyed peas (soaked in cold water for 8 hours) and added some cayenne pepper for kick. you could easily add spinach or cauliflower or even chicken or tofu. really good!

Rating: 3
This was very easy to prep and cook, yet had very complex flavors - particularly after it refrigerated overnight. If you have any onion-wary people in the house, you may want to trim down the amount you add. I doubled this recipe and served it over a black, nutty rice. Delicious!

